Items not included in the financial statement calculations but included in the presentation are referred to as parenthetical items. These usualy appear as a referenced item, or as a value in parenthesis describing that the value reported includes another specific amount. If the item is an additional disclosure in the income statement statement then make sure that is included as a child of one of the following abstract items: ShareBasedCompensationAllocationAndClassificationInFinancialStatementsAbstract, SupplementalIncomeStatementElementsAbstract
